# IAM Concepts Learned

## 1. Root Account vs IAM User

Root account has full access to AWS services and billing.

IAM users are created for limited and secure access.

---

## 2. Policies and Roles

Policies define permissions.

Roles provide temporary permissions for AWS services and users.

---

## 3. IAM User Groups

IAM groups help manage permissions for multiple users together.

---

## 4. Access Analyzer

Access Analyzer helps identify external or public access permissions.

---

## 5. Identity Providers

Identity Providers help users log in using external authentication systems.

---

## 6. Root Access Management

Root account should not be used daily because it has unrestricted permissions.

